{{ja-kanjitab|たち|yomi=o}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=たち|-}}. Appears in the ''{{w|Man'yōshū}}'', completed some time after 759 CE.<ref>{{RQ:Manyoshu|19|4240}}, text [http://jti.lib.virginia.edu/japanese/manyoshu/Man19Yo.html#4240 here]</ref>

The ultimate derivation is {{unk|ja|nocap=1|sort=たち}}, but this might be a nativized borrowing from {{bor|ja|ltc|sort=たち|達|tr={{IPAchar|/dɑt̚/|}}|pos=perhaps from the “general, common; everywhere, all over” senses?}}, possibly cognate with {{cog|ko|들|pos=plural marker}}.

The ''tachi'' reading is analyzed by some references<ref>Jim Breen's WWWJDIC, {{m|ja|達}} character entry [http://nihongo.monash.edu/cgi-bin/wwwjdic?1MMC%E9%81%94 here]</ref> as [[訓読み#Japanese|kun'yomi]] or a native-Japanese reading. Alternatively, this might be a shift from the [[呉音#Japanese|goon]] reading of ''dachi''.

